law.text:
The factors that the Commission shall consider in deciding whether to grant a permit shall include:
the needs and convenience of the public;
whether the satellite simulcast facility:
would be expected to interfere unreasonably with attendance at tracks; and
meets the requirements of § 11-825(a) of this subtitle;
the desires of the political subdivision where the proposed satellite simulcast facility is to be located;
the interests of the racing industry; and
other matters that the Commission finds appropriate.
